Document: InputMap
Path: godot/classes/class_inputmap.rst
Summary: Manages all the actions and their associated input events.

InputMap is the global singleton that manages all the input actions and their associated input events. You can define new actions and bind keys, mouse buttons, joystick buttons, or axis movements to them.

Inherits: Object < Object

Methods:
Action: action_add_event(action: StringName, event: InputEvent)
Adds an InputEvent to the given action.

Action: action_erase_events(action: StringName)
Removes all InputEvents from the given action.

Action: action_get_events(action: StringName)
Returns an array of InputEvents associated with the given action.

Action: action_has_event(action: StringName, event: InputEvent)
Returns true if the action contains the given InputEvent.

Action: action_set_deadzone(action: StringName, deadzone: float)
Sets the deadzone for a joystick axis action. The deadzone is the amount of movement required to register an input.

Action: has_action(action: StringName)
Returns true if the action exists.

Action: load_from_file(path: String)
Loads the input map from a file.

Action: save_to_file(path: String)
Saves the input map to a file.

Action: string_to_action(action: StringName, make_new: bool = false)
Converts a string to an action name. If make_new is true, a new action will be created if the action does not exist.

Action: action_to_string(action: StringName)
Converts an action name to a string.

Action: erase_action(action: StringName)
Removes the action from the input map.

Action: get_actions()
Returns an array of all action names.

Action: action_press(action: StringName)
Simulates pressing an action.

Action: action_release(action: StringName)
Simulates releasing an action.

Action: action_is_pressed(action: StringName)
Returns true if the action is currently pressed.

Action: action_get_force(action: StringName)
Returns the force of the action (e.g., for analog inputs).

Action: action_get_vector(action: StringName)
Returns the vector of the action (e.g., for joystick input).

Action: action_set_transform(action: StringName, transform: Transform2D)
Sets the transform for a joystick axis action. This is used to remap the axes.

Action: action_get_deadzone(action: StringName)
Returns the deadzone for a joystick axis action.

Action: action_get_transform(action: StringName)
Returns the transform for a joystick axis action.

Action: add_joy_mapping(guid: String, mapping: String)
Adds a joystick mapping. This allows you to map specific joystick buttons and axes to actions.

Action: remove_joy_mapping(guid: String)
Removes a joystick mapping.

Action: is_joy_known(guid: String)
Returns true if the joystick is known.

Action: get_joy_guid(device: int)
Returns the GUID of the joystick at the given device index.

Action: get_joy_axis_count(device: int)
Returns the number of axes on the joystick at the given device index.

Action: get_joy_button_count(device: int)
Returns the number of buttons on the joystick at the given device index.

Action: get_joy_hat_count(device: int)
Returns the number of hats on the joystick at the given device index.

Action: get_joy_name(device: int)
Returns the name of the joystick at the given device index.

Action: get_joy_mapping(guid: String)
Returns the mapping for the given joystick GUID.

Action: get_joy_axis_index_from_string(axis: String)
Converts a string representation of an axis to its integer index.

Action: get_joy_button_index_from_string(button: String)
Converts a string representation of a button to its integer index.

Action: get_joy_hat_index_from_string(hat: String)
Converts a string representation of a hat to its integer index.

Action: get_joy_axis_string_from_index(axis: int)
Converts an integer index of an axis to its string representation.

Action: get_joy_button_string_from_index(button: int)
Converts an integer index of a button to its string representation.

Action: get_joy_hat_string_from_index(hat: int)
Converts an integer index of a hat to its string representation.

Action: get_joy_axis_value(device: int, axis: int)
Returns the value of the joystick axis at the given device index and axis index.

Action: get_joy_button_value(device: int, button: int)
Returns the value of the joystick button at the given device index and button index.

Action: get_joy_hat_value(device: int, hat: int)
Returns the value of the joystick hat at the given device index and hat index.

Action: get_joy_device_count()
Returns the number of connected joysticks.

